  "prompt": "What is a Walmart Rollback? What are they for?",
  "response": "A Walmart Rollback is a temporary price reduction on a specific item, offered by Walmart. Think of it as a short-term sale or a limited-time offer.\n\n**What they are for:**\n\n*   **Driving Sales:** Rollbacks are primarily used to increase sales volume. The lower price attracts more customers, and the limited-time nature of the offer can create a sense of urgency, encouraging people to buy immediately.\n\n*   **Clearing Inventory:** Rollbacks can be used to reduce overstocked items or make way for new products.\n\n*   **Attracting Customers:** The discounted price can bring new customers to Walmart and encourage existing customers to buy more.\n\n*   **Competitive Pricing:** Rollbacks help Walmart stay competitive with other retailers by offering lower prices on popular items.\n\n*   **Promoting Specific Items:** Rollbacks can be used to promote specific brands or products that Walmart wants to highlight.\n\nIn essence, Rollbacks are a marketing tactic used by Walmart to boost sales and attract customers by offering temporary discounts on various products.",
